ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: The course covers a lot of good material, but I think the final project is the most rewarding and instructive component of the course.
I would definitely recommend this course.
I would certainly recommend this class to other students who want to become familiar with or review or appreciate microwave circuits.

Great class, definitely required for working with microwave circuits. The material might seem daunting at first but the class explains everything from first principles so by the end of it you will have a good understanding of the limitations in microwave circuit design.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Very applicable to my current research.
This course will directly contribute to my working knowledge needed on a day to day basis in my research.
It makes me have better understanding for circuits design and the instruments I am using.
